2026-04-10: Added data_capture_viewer.py — tkinter GUI to browse CSV/Excel under NewMotorController, stacked time-series with shared X and file/series navigation; requirements.txt gains pandas + openpyxl.
2026-04-11: vesc_serial_control.py and vescUartTest.ino — dropped USB serial host path; control is BLE-only; removed pyserial from requirements.
2026-04-11: vesc_serial_control.py — live plots use latest sample time as window end (TELEM vs ENC alignment); faster UI pump / BLE line wait / TELEM poll default; CSV adds device_ms and t_rel_s from ESP32 millis capture window.
2026-04-11: vesc_serial_control.py — CSV export is now time-aligned wide rows: one row per TELEM sample (slowest stream) with nearest ENC snapshot paired by device_ms (±50ms); no more stream column. Falls back to ENC-only rows if Live TELEM was off.
2026-04-11: vesc_serial_control.py — drop enc_skew_ms column; TELEM poll floor 5 ms (spinbox 5–5000); live “Actual: XX Hz (NN ms)” readout next to TELEM interval so user can probe BLE TELEM ceiling.
2026-04-11: vesc_serial_control.py — merge encoder position/velocity into the main live figure (5 equal-height subplots: Pos, Vel, RPM, Vbat, A); drop separate encoder figure and its LabelFrame.
2026-04-20: vescUartTest.ino — BLE sendBleRaw uses 180-byte chunks (one notify per TELEM/ENC line at MTU 247) and drops the 3 ms per-chunk delay that was blocking loop(); loop() tick delay trimmed 2→1 ms. Clears the ~12 ms/TELEM and ~6 ms/ENC self-throttle that capped polling at ~200 ms with ENC on.
2026-04-20: vesc_serial_control.py — default quiet log (TELEM/ENC/OK/[READY] skipped from text pane; Verbose log checkbox to restore) + Link status indicator dots (Ready heartbeat, Motor OK pulse on SET_*/KEEPALIVE, Stop pulse on OK,STOP, latching Error on ERROR,*). Removes the Tk-append backlog that caused the "graph freezes then catches up" burst at fast polling.
2026-04-20: vesc_serial_control.py — TELEM poll is now fixed-rate (next send = last_send + interval, wall-clock), not fixed-delay after response. Added pile-up guard so sub-RTT intervals cap at firmware RTT cleanly instead of queuing requests. Observed aim/actual was interval+~40 ms (one BLE round-trip + VESC UART RTT); now actual equals aim when aim ≥ RTT floor.
2026-04-20: vesc_serial_control.py — new "CSV on uniform time grid" checkbox (default on). CSV rows are emitted on a uniform device_ms grid (step = TELEM-poll ms) with nearest-neighbor TELEM + ENC, so t_rel_s deltas are exactly constant regardless of BLE/VESC jitter. Live graphs keep raw samples; grid is export-only.
2026-04-20: vescUartTest.ino — BLE connection interval: fixed the setMinPreferred/setMinPreferred copy-paste (was overwriting itself) so advertising now requests 7.5–15 ms preferred, and onConnect actively calls updateConnParams(6,12) to negotiate a tight interval with the central. Reduces the ~15 ms offset on TELEM cadence that showed up at poll intervals below 150 ms (one BLE connection event of latency per direction).
2026-04-20: vesc_serial_control.py — combined the Live TELEM and Encoder control rows into one "Live streams + plots" LabelFrame (one row for TELEM poll, one for ENC stream + graph window). Added a separate CSV grid ms spinbox decoupled from TELEM-poll ms, so you can poll fast and still write CSV at a sane cadence (e.g. poll 30 ms, CSV 100 ms).
2026-04-20: vesc_serial_control.py — ENC live-rate readout (Hz + mean ms) next to the ENC stream checkbox, computed the same way as the TELEM readout (device_ms deltas of the last 2 s). Makes it easy to tell if ENC is actually hitting the firmware's 100 Hz target or being throttled by BLE/loop jitter.
2026-04-20: data_capture_viewer.py — new "Sampling rate + uniformity" panel at the top. For each loaded CSV it shows mean/median/stdev/min/max/jitter (max-min) of the time deltas for four streams: overall CSV row cadence, TELEM-present rows, ENC-paired rows, and the raw ENC firmware stream (unique enc_device_ms). Each block also reports Hz and a UNIFORM / near-uniform / jittery / irregular verdict so you can verify at a glance whether the export is actually evenly spaced.
2026-04-20: vesc_serial_control.py — Link status strip now has a live "Run: TEST/RUN  elapsed / total s" readout (250 ms tick), so you can see at a glance whether a timed Test or motor run is active and how much of it is left. Also moved the CSV grid ms setting out of the Timed-output frame and into the Live-streams frame so all sampling cadences (TELEM poll, ENC stream, CSV grid) are grouped together.
2026-04-20: data_capture_viewer.py — stats panel was white-on-white in macOS dark mode because the Text widget inherited the LabelFrame's dynamic system background but kept Tk's default foreground. Forced explicit near-white bg / near-black fg so the uniformity report is readable under every system theme.
2026-04-20: vesc_serial_control.py — widened grid-mode TELEM pairing tolerance from max(grid_ms, 40) to max(grid_ms + poll_ms, 2*grid_ms, 120). A single dropped poll at 100 ms / 125 ms grid now still fills the grid cell instead of blanking it. Grid-mode CSV log also reports the TELEM-fill ratio + tolerance alongside the ENC pairing stats. CSV filenames gain millisecond precision (…_HHMMSS_mmm_…) so the stamp is unambiguous per export and back-to-back Test runs can't collide.
2026-04-20: data_capture_viewer.py — replaced the "one series at a time" toggle with a per-graph checkbox panel: one checkbox per numeric column, rebuilt on every file load, with All on / All off / Solo current shortcuts. Up/Down and PgUp/PgDn now cycle a "solo" pointer through the series (one graph at a time) while still respecting the checkbox state. Columns that persist across file reloads keep their previous visibility so you don't have to re-uncheck the same series every time you navigate.
2026-04-20: vesc_serial_control.py — bumped default sampling cadences to match the values that produced clean UNIFORM captures: TELEM poll 50→100 ms (on or just above the BLE/VESC RTT floor) and CSV grid 50→125 ms (≥ poll so every grid cell reliably finds a fresh TELEM). Fresh launches now open on a known-good config instead of an over-aggressive 50/50.
2026-04-20: vescUartTest.ino + vesc_serial_control.py — TELEM is now firmware-streamed (TELEM_STREAM,<on>[,<ms>]) instead of host-polled via GET_VALUES; ENC_STREAM gains an optional interval arg (ENC_STREAM,<on>[,<ms>]). One BLE notify per sample instead of request+response kills the ~30 ms macOS CI penalty that set the old ~100 ms floor; practical cadence now ~25–30 ms for TELEM. Python UI: "Live TELEM poll" renamed to "Firmware TELEM stream", default 30 ms; new ENC interval spinbox (default 10 ms) next to the ENC checkbox so you can back ENC off to 20 ms when TELEM is streaming so they don't fight for notify slots. Interval spinboxes auto-apply (250 ms debounce) — no Apply button. GET_VALUES still works as one-shot.
